South Korea Stocks: Hynix Semiconductor, Kolon Industries

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-07-05T06:30:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/kolon-industries-korea-electric-power-korea-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in South Korea trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close in  Seoul .  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  advanced 16.45, or 0.8 percent, to
2,161.75. The gauge rose for a fifth day, its longest winning
streak since April.  Hynix Semiconductor Inc. (000660)  (000660 KS), the world’s second-
largest computer-memory chipmaker, rallied 3.9 percent to 28,000
won, rising for a third day. Hyundai Heavy Industries Co.
(009540 KS) plans to submit a preliminary bid to buy a stake in
Hynix by the July 8 deadline, MoneyToday reported, citing
industry officials it didn’t identify.  Hyundai Heavy, the world’s biggest shipyard, is undecided
on whether to bid for a stake in Hynix, the company said in a
mobile-phone text message sent to Bloomberg News. Hyundai Heavy
retreated 1.3 percent to 455,000 won.  Kolon Industries Inc. (120110)  (120110 KS), a chemical fibers maker,
added 2.7 percent to 114,500 won, after advancing as much as 4.5
percent earlier. The company had its share-price estimate raised
to 160,000 won from 130,000 won at Tong Yang Securities Inc.,
which cited a stronger earnings outlook and attractive
valuations, according to a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
 sshin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
